        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 6:58PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Beckville to near Carthage to near Garrison to
near Huntington. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Deberry, Melrose, Front, Elysian Fields, Jericho, Stockman,
Nacogdoches, Fairplay, Chireno, Carthage, Midyett, Tatum, Deadwood,
Dotson, Martinsville, Bland Lake, Neuville, Appleby, Center, and
Broaddus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for
eastern and northeastern Texas.</instruction>
